comment_data.body:
There is just one problem with running all examples with `cython -3`, last week the bind [`_Py_REFCNT` was added](https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/6152) and I didn't find any mention of this in the change log to the next release. 

So, running [`parameter_refcount`](https://github.com/cython/cython/blob/master/docs/examples/userguide/language_basics/parameter_refcount.pyx#L1) examples the output was: `'cpython/ref/_Py_REFCNT.pxd' not found`.  Is that something that I should have in my local env?

comment_data.body:
Thanks

> There is just one problem with running all examples with `cython -3`, last week the bind [`_Py_REFCNT` was added](https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/6152) and I didn't find any mention of this in the change log to the next release.
> 
> So, running [`parameter_refcount`](https://github.com/cython/cython/blob/master/docs/examples/userguide/language_basics/parameter_refcount.pyx#L1) examples the output was: `'cpython/ref/_Py_REFCNT.pxd' not found`. Is that something that I should have in my local env?

I think this is just because you're testing these with an older version of Cython that doesn't have the change. The easiest way to fix it is probably to directly call the cython.py from the git repo instead of calling "cython" (which links to whatever's installed).

milestone.description:
* Remove code for Python 2 and Python < 3.7.
* Integrate better with Python 3.
* Improve support for the Limited API.
* Start supporting GIL-free Python 3.13.
* Support the Py3.13 `sys.monitoring` API.
